{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And it came to pass afterward, that he went throughout every city and village, preaching and shewing the glad tidings of the kingdom of God: and the twelve were with him"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And certain women, which had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities, Mary called Magdalene, out of whom went seven devils"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Joanna the wife of Chuza Herod's steward, and Susanna, and many others, which ministered unto him of their substance"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when much people were gathered together, and were come to him out of every city, he spake by a parable"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Parable of the Sower"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when he had said these things"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "he cried",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "What might this parable be?",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then came to him his mother and his brethren, and could not come at him for the press"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus' Mother and Brothers"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Now it came to pass on a certain day, that he went into a ship with his disciples"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "And he said unto them",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they launched forth"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Calming of the Storm"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Master, master, we perish",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        },
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then he arose, and rebuked the wind and the raging of the water: and they ceased, and there was a calm"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou Son of God most high? I beseech thee, torment me not",
          "speaker": "Demon-possessed man"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Healing of the Demon-Possessed Man"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And, behold, there came a man named Jairus, and he was a ruler of the synagogue: and he fell down at Jesus' feet, and besought him that he would come into his house"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Healing of Jairus' Daughter"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 45,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "When all denied",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Master, the multitude throng thee and press thee, and sayest thou",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 48,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "he said unto her",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 50,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "he answered him, saying",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}